The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport
		 Tuesday, August 10, 2004  IN THE CITY
				 																																																	 Bengal tennis player Puja Paul has received a scholarship from an academy in Missouri. A student of the city-based Tennis UnLtd Academy, she is the first girl from the state to have achieved the feat. Meanwhile, Paul Dale, Thailands national coach, will visit the city academy for a week-long coaching camp in December.				 																																																	 Naru Gopal Ghosh of West Bengal Police scored a hattrick in the CFL first division group A match against Kalighat Club in Kalyani on Monday. The policemen won the match 3-0.
